<subSubSection id="C347B4D9012BFFC56F82FE86D94DB565" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE2E752012BFFC56F82FE86D94DB565" blockId="16.[151,1435,152,364]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B9293B40012BFFC56F82FE86D96BB54E" bold="true" box="[198,343,301,327]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet, 
<emphasis id="B9293B40012BFFC56D1CFE86DA94B54F" box="[600,680,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">aurora</emphasis>
, a Latin adjective meaning sunrise, refers to the orange colored postmedian fascia.
</paragraph>
